I was expected this to be the behaviour of the "Calendars" button in the global header.

As I was creating this feedback ticket, my original summary was going to be: "Why can't I see the Confluence Development team calendar when I click on 'Calendars' in the header?"

It wasn't until I went back to [Sherif's blog post|https://pug.jira.com/wiki/display/CONFDEV/2013/11/04/The+Confluence+Team+is+moving+to+use+Team+Calendars] to access the calendar that I saw the link to add it to my calendar list.

There also doesn't seem to be a way to add the calendar to "my calendar list" while viewing a page where the calendar is embedded (did I miss it?) - although I didn't even think to look for this when I was originally wondering how to get the calendar to display on {code}/calendar/mycalendar.action{code}

