The creator of a calendar will not receive notifications of events added to that calendar.

This is because DefaultCalendarNotificationManager.java contains code that checks whether the creator is subscribed to the _child_ calendar, not the parent calendar. When a user creates a calendar, it does not create subscriptions to the child calendars (eg Events, Leave etc). When a user adds a calendar created by someone else, it does create subscriptions to the child calendars. The code that determines whether a user is subscribed to a calendar that they did not create actually checks against the parent, where the code that checks if the creator is watching the calendar checks against the child. This can never return true, so creators will never receive notifications.

